olitical economy and humanistic perspectives on issues of existential meaning. The chapters, from a wide range of contributors, focus on major issues in ageing such as autonomy, agency, frailty, lifestyle, social isolation, dementia and professional challenges in social work and participatory research. This volume should be valuable reading for scholars and graduate students in gerontology and humanistic studies, as well as for policy makers and practitioners working in the field of ageing.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aAgingxSocial aspects. 0aAging. 0aGerontology. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Gerontology.2bisacsh1 aBaars, Jan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBaars, Jan, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBruens, Margreet Th., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDannefer, Dale, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDohmen, Joseph, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDohmen, Joseph, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGrenier, Amanda, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGrenier, Amanda, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHortulanus, Roelof, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLaceulle, Hanne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLin, Jielu, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMachielse, Anja, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPhillipson, Chris, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPhillipson, Chris, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aRay, Mo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relat